FBIS4-55927 "dreeu101__a94017" FBIS-EEU-94-101-A Daily Report 20 May 1994 ANNEX Poland Pawlak Accepts Resignation of Reform Official Pawlak Accepts Resignation of Reform Official LD2005133194 Warsaw PAP in English 1115 GMT 20 May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD2005133194 Warsaw PAP English BFN [Text] Warsaw, May 20 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak on Friday accepted the resignation of Government Commissioner for Public Administration Reform Michal Kulesza, the commissioner's bureau reported. Kulesza was appointed for the post in autumn 1992 by Hanna Suchocka who was Poland's prime minister at the time. He submitted his resignation at the beginning of this week, blaming the government with stopping systemic reforms in Poland .
